while remaining matter.

Through gravitational compression (r → r_s): the Pauli floor in the
imaginary sector halts compression. Matter bounces at the floor radius.

**What needs to be derived:**

A formal topological proof that no continuous deformation of the PMV
state can move a particle from d² > 0 to d² = 0 while preserving m > 0.

