## IX.5 The Universe as a Standing Wave

The choke point between the +i outer universe and the −i inner
anti-universe is a node of the cosmic wavefunction:

```
At the node:  Ψ = (+i) + (−i) = 0    [addition — destructive interference]
              dΨ/dt = Aω ≠ 0          [the bounce energy, angular momentum]
```

The correct operation at the node is **addition**, not multiplication.
Wavefunctions superpose — they add. The result is zero: a node passing
through zero on its way to the other side, not a product creating a
real output. The bounce is the passage through zero driven by the
kinetic energy in dΨ/dt ≠ 0.

**Why the bounce is inevitable:**

For a true singularity the wavefunction must stop at zero: dΨ/dt = 0.
This requires zero angular momentum at the node — perfect spherical
symmetry. The uncertainty principle forbids this. The bounce is quantum
mechanically guaranteed.

**The synchronization problem dissolved:**

The +i and −i cones arrive at the node at potentially different
coordinate times. At the node the metric vanishes and all proper
time is zero: Δτ = 0. The wait literally does not exist as a duration.

**What needs to be derived:**

The frequency ω of the cosmic standing wave as a function of the
total energy-momentum content — giving a prediction for the period of
the cosmic cycle testable against H₀ and the cosmological density.

